<p><a name="Works" id="Works"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=William_Playfair&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Works">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Works</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>1786. <i>The Commercial and Political Atlas: Representing, by Means of Stained Copper-Plate Charts, the Progress of the Commerce, Revenues, Expenditure and Debts of England during the Whole of the Eighteenth Century</i>.</li>
<li>1801. <i>Statistical Breviary; Shewing, on a Principle Entirely New, the Resources of Every State and Kingdom in Europe</i>. London: Wallis.</li>
<li>1805. <i>A Statistical Account of the United States of America by D. F. Donnant</i>. London: J. Whiting. William Playfair, Trans.</li>
<li>1807. <i>An Inquiry into the Permanent Causes of the Decline and Fall of Powerful and Wealthy Nations: Designed To Shew How The Prosperity Of The British Empire May Be Prolonged</i>.</li>
</ul>
